        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 6:24PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 623 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Las Animas, or 19 miles east of North La Junta, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Las Animas and John Martin Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
